review:
This is such a downgrade from Salt & Sanctuary. I understand trying to spice the formula by meshing mechanics from other games (Monster Hunter) but you can't just add things willy nilly.

- The mages you hunt is basically the same with a different coat of paint;
- The other bosses are all forgettable with simplistic moveset;
- Bosses are simplistic, but they don't have stamina and spam the sh** out of their AoE high damaging attacks;
- So, bosses spam attacks, your dodge consumes a lot of stamina and, the cherry on top, dodge covers a lot of ground, positioning you far from the boss so you can hit once, maybe twice before the boss start another attack;
- 90% of the attacks will send you flying or juggle you for potential combos, Tekken style;
- There's no map, which is not bad by itself, but when you need to chase mages around, it gets really tedious;
- Since you have to chase mages around, you still have to deal with trash mobs that can still kill you easily;
- Exploration is gutted, making the gear you use behind grinding mages materials;
- Grappling hook is very inconsistent. Don't know if it's my controller, but I fell to my death so much from this because the hook flashed for 1s and it didn't register the input. Don't have this problem in other games though.

4.5/10

I stopped after beating the Mech mage, whatever his name is, in Corvious Mire, so a don't know about the rest of the game, but i'm not willing to waste maybe another 10-20h to find out.

I read the mixed reviews from steam release before buying and waited for a good sale.
Payed dirt cheap and still got disappointed. What a shame, it blows my mind that this came from the creators of the amazing Salt & Sanctuary.
Another one on my list of "will never finish".
